Andes originated as a Rust port of MS-GF+. Its scoring code has since been
clean-room reauthored and the generating function removed, but the bundled
statistical models (resources/ionstat/models.parquet) are still derived from
MS-GF+'s released parameter files. While those models ship, Andes remains a
derivative work and is distributed under the same terms as the upstream MS-GF+
software (The Regents of the University of California). The full upstream
license text is reproduced verbatim below.

See ./NOTICE for the precise, component-by-component derivation status and the
intent to relicense once all bundled models are independently trained.

